wikipedia_page.main: Edward Gaskell (19 December 1916 – 10 February 2009) was an English professional football goalkeeper, coach and manager. He is best remembered for his time in the Football League with Brentford, with whom he had a 15-year association as a player and coach. He also held coaching positions at non-league clubs Hendon, Wealdstone, Southall and with the Football Association at Lilleshall.
